Not even close.

76
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,880
This one looks like you!

77
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:04,840
Not at all.

78
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,520
Yours doesn't look like me at all!

79
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:07,280
Mine looks like you!

80
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:08,400
Yours is so chubby!

81
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,240
Easy.

82
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:13,960
Chui!

83
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:14,840
Catch me if you can!

84
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:16,400
It's snowing, take this!

85
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,400
[My beloved,]

86
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,920
you've always loved the winter snow.

87
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:08,720
You once said,

88
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,280
that snow is the purest,

89
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,680
capable of covering all the

90
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:18,080
filth and ugliness.

91
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,280
My beloved,

92
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,240
how have I conducted

93
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:27,560
myself in your stead?

94
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,400
[Are you content?]

95
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,880
I am unaware of

96
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:38,920
any mistakes I may have made.

97
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,240
[When we]

98
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:43,920
reunite in

99
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,000
the netherworld,

100
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,080
will you blame me?

101
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:03,520
Your Highness!

102
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:11,560
The incense smoke

103
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:14,520
stung my eyes.

104
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:17,440
Why are you back?

105
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:19,040
Didn't I ask you to

106
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,200
take a break for the festival?

107
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:22,640
Wan is already

108
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,120
accustomed to handling daily affairs.

109
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,080
Now that I have time off,

110
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,520
[I find it quite boring.]

111
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:29,400
Wan finds this snowy night

112
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,960
to be quite dull and lonely,

113
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,520
so I invited Mr. Jin to join me,

114
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,880
[hoping to entertain]

115
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:36,360
[Your Highness.]

116
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,600
Girl...

117
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,000
I know

118
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,280
you must feel that I

119
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:43,200
am solitary and heartbroken,

120
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,680
so you intentionally find

121
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:47,280
comforting words to console me.

122
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:49,240
Your Highness,

123
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,280
I have just composed a new melody

124
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:52,680
[titled "Melancholy and Mirth."]

125
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,200
I wonder if Your Highness

126
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,600
would care to hear it?

127
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,800
Prepare a feast.

128
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,640
For today we shall

129
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,560
eat and drink heartily,

130
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:05,720
just like the ordinary households,

131
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,600
and celebrate the Winter Solstice

132
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,080
with warmth and joy!

133
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:29,880
Don't melt! Don't melt!

134
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:31,720
You are not allowed to melt!

135
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,160
No!

136
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:42,920
No!

137
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,040
You are meant to be mine.

138
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:48,480
Mine!

139
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:04,880
I will not allow anyone

140
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:07,120
to snatch away what's meant for me!

141
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,440
Never!

142
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:34,600
Good.

143
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:37,480
Please.

144
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:45,760
Your Royal Highness,

145
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,000
Chancellor Lai requests an audience.

146
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:49,440
Summon him!

147
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:54,320
What brings him here

148
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,080
on such a snowy night?

149
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,320
Chancellor Lai,

150
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:09,680
[what could be so urgent]

151
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:12,320
that you've ventured out

152
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:14,320
on this snowy holiday eve?

153
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:15,640
Your Royal Highness,

154
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,880
I have just received an anonymous tip-off

155
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:18,960
stating that Yan Xing

156
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,440
was specifically arranged by Lord Zhang

157
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:21,800
to marry Lord Shen

158
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,360
[with the intention of winning him over.]

159
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,440
On the day of the winter solstice,

160
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:26,200
Lord Zhang even used the safety of the Yans

161
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,240
to coerce Yan Xing into compliance.

162
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:32,640
This is someone

163
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,720
trying to create trouble for no reason!

164
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:38,960
Does Yan Xing truly belong

165
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:41,080
to Prince Xian's faction?

166
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,400
[Your Highness,]

167
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:43,600
I'm afraid that

168
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,080
there may be some misunderstanding.

169
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:46,760
The tip-off also mentioned

170
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,320
[that originally, Your Highness]

171
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,400
[granted a marriage decree]

172
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,840
[to the third daughter of the Yan Family,]

173
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,520
[but the Yan Family, with ulterior motives,]

174
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:53,600
[switched her with Xing.]

175
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,000
Now this Yan Xing has been promoted

176
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,960
to Chief Clerk of the Ministry of Justice.

177
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:58,760
[It is evident that the Yans' intentions]

178
00:15:58,760 --> 00:15:59,920
[in this are treacherous!]

179
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:01,960
[Could Yan Xing's allegiance]

180
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:03,920
truly lie with Prince Xian?

181
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:07,680
Your Highness,

182
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:09,880
[Jin Zang humbly speaks.]

183
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,640
The sixth daughter, Yan Xing

184
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,200
is my niece.

185
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:14,800
[She has always dreamed of dedicating]

186
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,880
[herself to the imperial court]

187
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,720
[as a female detective.]

188
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,240
[Despite an unexpected marriage]

189
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,160
to the Shen Family,

190
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:23,200
her loyalty and sincerity

191
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,160
remain untainted.

192
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,680
[Please see her true nature, Your Highness.]

193
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,240
Jin Zang,

194
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:32,240
you have been permitted to perform in

195
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:34,800
my chamber for many years.

196
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:37,560
Meddling in state affairs, a new boldness!

197
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:40,440
I wouldn't dare, Your Highness.

198
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,000
Lord Lai,

199
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,880
regarding Yan Xing,

200
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:48,560
is it worth your late-night visit?

201
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,080
If you have any more urgent matters,

202
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,280
speak them all out at once.

203
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,440
I have just learned that

204
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,000
in Xiang'an City,

205
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:57,920
a nursery rhyme has suddenly spread,

206
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,560
[and it sounds quite inappropriate.]

207
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,840
A nursery rhyme?

208
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,280
Red porridge and dates,

209
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,000
five feet from the heaven.

210
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:06,920
[Citruses and loquats,]

211
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:08,200
[hard for lad to grasp.]

212
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:09,600
[Do not speak recklessly.]

213
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:10,840
[Who says,]

214
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:11,920
[granny is angry,]

215
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:13,200
[salt rises.]

216
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,000
Lady Xu is clever and graceful,

217
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:15,920
and she has clearly identified

218
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:16,880
the issues within.

219
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:19,160
[It directly targets Your Highness,]

220
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,520
["five feet from the heaven."]

221
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:21,560
"Hard for lad to grasp."

222
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:22,960
This is a blatant disrespect

223
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,640
to both Your Highness and His Majesty!

224
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:26,080
Insolence!

225
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:27,520
Such a rhyme

226
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,000
could not have appeared without reason.

227
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:29,760
[There must be wicked schemers]

228
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:31,120
plotting behind the scenes.

229
00:17:31,199 --> 00:17:32,760
I urge Your Highness to take action!

230
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,080
Can we uncover

231
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:45,120
who is spreading such slander?

232
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,880
It's challenging to trace the source,

233
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:50,040
as it circulates among the children.

234
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,200
After all these years...

235
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,040
I have dedicated myself

236
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:07,960
wholeheartedly to the Xiao Family's reign,

237
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,800
[yet there are always those who suspect]

238
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,640
I act out of selfish motives.

239
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,000
To exploit a nursery rhyme

240
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:17,800
to manipulate public sentiment

241
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:20,360
is truly despicable!

242
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:22,520
We'll launch a full-scale investigation

243
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:23,960
immediately to ensure that we

244
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,760
take down the mastermind!

245
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:28,320
But...

246
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:29,800
What?

247
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,400
However, the melody used in this rhyme

248
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,240
was composed by Mr. Jin

249
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:35,120
[for the winter solstice banquet]

250
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,760
[at Prince Xian's residence.]

251
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,920
This melody is

252
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:40,440
titled "Melancholy and Mirth."

253
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,560
Your Royal Highness,

254
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,160
this piece was created by me

255
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:52,080
to honor the Winter Solstice.

256
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:54,880
[It was indeed performed for the first time]

257
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:55,920
[during the feast at the prince's residence.]

258
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,640
[However, this piece has no lyrics,]

259
00:18:59,080 --> 00:19:01,200
and certainly no disloyal intentions.

260
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:02,920
But if the player

261
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,640
[is unintentional,]

262
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:05,840
[what if the listener has ulterior motives?]

263
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,400
[That last line of the rhyme,]

264
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:08,800
"granny is angry,"

265
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:09,960
"salt rises."

266
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,680
the "salt (xian)" in this line

267
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:13,440
likely refers to Prince Xian!

268
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:20,120
Summon Prince Xian!

269
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,680
Mother!

270
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:28,160
I am unaware!

271
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,480
I am being wronged!

272
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:30,400
[Regarding "Melancholy and Mirth,"]

273
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:32,280
I first heard it

274
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,160
during the banquet.

275
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:34,200
I didn't pay much attention at the time,

276
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:35,160
and I had no idea

277
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:37,080
that someone would seize this opportunity

278
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:38,920
to add lyrics that allude to Your Highness!

279
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:39,960
I firmly believe

280
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:41,520
this is not the doing of Mr. Jin,

281
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,840
nor is it instigated by His Highness.

282
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,160
[However, this piece was]

283
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:47,240
[just performed at the prince's residence]

284
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:48,600
and immediately had rebellious lyrics

285
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:49,920
added, spreading through the streets.

286
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,320
Moreover,

287
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:53,280
the ending of this rhyme clearly implies

288
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,680
that His Highness seeks advancement.

289
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,040
I urge you, mother, to see clearly

